<a href="08.htm"><img border="0" src="next.gif" width="26" height="26"></a></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="5">3. Publish components with specifications</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:.25in"><font size="4">- Component 
producer, on completion of software component, should make it &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;available.</font></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in" type="disc">
  <li class="MsoNormal"><font size="4">Component specification not already 
  published:</font></li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:.5in"><font size="4">- Publish 
specification, implementation, and executable at the same time.</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="4">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - Only specification, if 
producer plans to charge for use of component.</font></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in" type="disc">
  <li class="MsoNormal"><font size="4">Component specification already exists in 
  the library:</font></li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:.5in"><font size="4">- Specification 
matches finished component, then synchronize the two to form usable component.</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:.5in"><font size="4">- Specification no 
longer matches the finished component, then it needs to be updated to reflect 
changes.&nbsp;</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:.25in"><font size="4">- Four levels of 
component abstraction within component library:</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="4">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1.&nbsp; Component Specification</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="4">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2.&nbsp; Component Implementation</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="4">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3.&nbsp; Component Executable</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="4">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 4.&nbsp; Component Deployment&nbsp;</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:.25in"><font size="4">Maintain 
dependency links between levels for:</font></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in" type="disc">
  <li class="MsoNormal"><font size="4">Checking impact of changes before they 
  are made.</font></li>
  <li class="MsoNormal"><font size="4">Determining in what programs software 
  components have been used.</font></li>
</ul>

</body>

